description_bullet: 12.5oz Japanese Stretch Selvedge Denim,98% Cotton / 2% Elastane,Made in Canada,SKU: 101022300
description_paragraph:
The Kasuri Stretch Selvedge is a 12.5oz Japanese denim with a red line selvedge ID. The warp yarns are dyed using the traditional Japanese Kasuri method. Cotton yarns are wrapped and bound tightly in sections before being dipped in indigo dye, so only the unbound sections can absorb the indigo. After each dip, the binding is removed and other sections are bound, and the yarn is dipped in indigo again. Dyers repeat this process several times to create warp yarns that each have an irregular unique spectrum of indigo shades, dipped to near black in some places and medium blue in others. Weaving these indigo yarns into white weft yarns creates a fabric with a stunning variety of indigo shades reminiscent of rain falling heavier and lighter in different places. Cut, sewn, built in Canada with contrast stitching, an oiled "crazy horse" leather patch, and silver metallic buttons and rivets. The Super Guy is a skinny fit with a medium rise, a slim top block, and a taper from knee to hem. 
 12.5oz Japanese Stretch Selvedge Denim

description_bullet: Japanese Fabric,Made in Canada,SKU: 101222200
description_paragraph:
The Sakiori Denim is a 16oz Japanese rag cloth made from recycled denim scraps. Sakiori weaving replaces warp yarns with fabric scraps. Each scrap of denim comes in its own shade of indigo and each one has edges that turn and fray. Over 250 years ago, Japanese peasants used Sakiori weaving to create whole rugs, garments from assorted scraps of fabric. With time and appreciation of the labor involved with making such irregular but invariably richly textured and colored cloth, such fabric became very expensive. 85% cotton, 15% acrylic. Bonded for durability. Cut, sewn, built in Canada with tonal stitching, a Navy Premium Suede patch, and silver metallic buttons and rivets. The Super Guy is a skinny fit with a medium rise, a slim top block, and a taper from knee to hem.

description_bullet: 11oz Japanese Duck Canvas,100% Cotton,Made in Canada,SKU: 101080000
description_paragraph:
The Indigo Tradition Canvas is an 11oz Japanese duck canvas with both the warp and weft rope-dyed in indigo vats. To create such a deep indigo shade, the yarns have to be dipped into indigo vats over and over and over again, never sitting in the dye long enough to permeate the core of the yarn. But with wear, the opposite process occurs, and the dips chip away layer by layer to reveal a rich spectrum of indigo that can be achieved through no other means.   To highlight this from the start the garment has been rinse washed, giving the fabric added texture and uncovering indigo tones from within the yarn.   Cut, sewn, built in Canada with tonal stitching, a Navy Full Grain leather patch, and black mil-spec non-reflective buttons and rivets. description_paragraph:
The Toxic Avenger Deformed Denim is a 14oz alternating twill denim woven in Japan with 100% organic cotton. The Toxic Avenger is an 80s B-movie turned cult classic. Its posters boast, “The first Super-Hero…from New Jersey!” Tale as old as time: 98-pounds of “solid nerd” is a janitor at a health club in Tromaville, New Jersey. Club members bully him constantly. In one stunt, they trick him into wearing a pink tutu, and he falls into toxic waste that deforms him and gives him superhuman size and strength. He keeps the tutu, takes his mop, fights crime and pollution, takes on the nickname “Toxie,” and saves Tromaville! This Deformed Denim alternates three different weaves to echo Toxie’s mutations: a right-hand twill, a left-hand twill, and a broken twill. Wild texture ripples through the fabric. The cotton is organic with a light green interior weft, so the Toxic Avenger will know he’s not alone in his fight against filth and injustice. Cut, sewn, built in Canada with contrast stitching, Toxie’s face embroidered on the back pocket, pink pocket bags – like his tutu – with a comic book screen print, a Natural Veg Tan with Black Foil Emboss leather patch, and metallic buttons and rivets. The Super Guy is a skinny fit with a medium rise, a slim top block, and a taper from knee to hem.

description_paragraph:
The True Grit Selvedge is a 15oz Unsanforized Japanese selvedge denim. Couple hairy, short-staple cotton yarns and rattly decades-old shuttle loom to get a denim grain this uneven and gritty. The brown cotton weft comes from using rare undyed natural brown cotton yarns, which gives the fabric a warm, earthy undertone. Look harder at the back of the cloth to notice different shades of brown in the weft. As cotton matures, its color changes greatly, so the varying brown hues reflect the different maturities of the cotton plants when they were harvested to make this yarn to make these jeans. Because of this, no two pairs of these will be the same and they will be unreproducible because every shade in the weft is a reflection of when each individual cotton plant was harvested.    NOTE  - Our estimated post soak measurement results were derived by machine hot washing and drying a single pair of jeans.  We did this to ensure maximum shrinkage.  We then collected the measurements post shrink, and  then calculated the percentage shrink rate across all measurement points.  We then applied the shrink rate percentage across all pre soak measurements and listed the results. We have found that the shrink rate was about 5%, less than typical unsanforized denims, though we suspect that some shrinkage occurred during production during the final press process which introduces steam and heat to the garment. In order to see if we could gain any extra length in the inseam we gently pulled the jeans and were able to add another .25" in the length (not indicated in the post soak measurements).  With wear all other measurements will likely stretch out by at least this much.

description_bullet: 17oz Japanese Selvedge Denim,100% Cotton,Made in Japan,SKU: 101567700
description_paragraph:
The MIJ7 – Yahan Midnight Selvedge is an unsanforized 17oz slubby Japanese selvedge denim dyed to such a deep shade of indigo that it appears black. Indigo rope dyeing is a delicate process of running cotton yarns through two story dye vats quickly enough that the dye cannot penetrate the core of the yarn. Then the yarn dries and is dipped again, dries and is dipped again. The yarns are dipped dozens of times to achieve that raw denim shade. But here, with just a little black dye added, these yarns have been dyed over and over so many times that they appear black. With wear and age, the opposite process occurs. Each layer of indigo chips away revealing dark blues, then medium bright blues, then light blues, then finally the white core of the yarn. This fabric is made to celebrate the full spectrum of variegated indigo shades. The yarns themselves are irregular, slubby, and woven loosely giving the fabric an organic, uneven grain. The denim is unsanforized but tempi treated, which shrinks the fabric but protects the hairiness, grittiness, and raw denim feel. The MIJ7 builds in the unparalleled detailing of the Made in Japan collection: black iron buttons that will rust, copper rivets that will oxidize, raised belt loops that will fade, a Japanese sheepskin leather patch with the “Flower of Carnage” logo, the MIJ maple leaf embroidered onto the back pocket, micro busted outseam, and a selvedge button fly. Dyed, woven, cut, sewn, built in Japan. The Super Guy is a skinny fit with a medium rise, a slim top block, and a taper from knee to hem. 
 17oz Japanese Selvedge Denim 
 100% Cotton 
 
 Made in Japan 
 SKU: 101567700
name: MIJ7 - Yahan Midnight Selvedge

description_bullet: 16oz Japanese Selvedge Denim,100% Cotton,Made in Japan,SKU: 101565600
description_paragraph:
The MIJ8 – Tokushima Natural Indigo Hand Dyed Intangible Cultural Treasure Selvedge Denim is a 16oz unsanforized Japanese selvedge denim hand dyed in Tokushima Japan, renowned worldwide for its indigo dyeing traditions. Only a handful of craftspeople in the world are trained in traditional Japanese hank dyeing. In this method, yarns are gathered into a bunch called a hank, and then dipped over and over again into a batch of natural indigo. Since the process is fully done by hand, every yard of fabric is unique. Natural indigo is created from the leaves of the indigo plant. While most indigo plants come from India, the traditional hank dye method only allows for the use of indigo grown on Japanese soil. Very little indigo is grown in Japan each year, making these jeans even more rare. Due to the lengthy fermentation process, it takes about 1 year to produce a new batch of natural Japanese indigo. The big slub yarns create a streaky irregular grain with thick cotton ridges rising out of the 3x1 twill. Check the weft to see the twill line distortion. The Unsanforized fabric avoids the standard finishing processes of heating, stretching, steaming, and singing to protect all of the natural character of the fabric, but it is preshrunk using tempi-treatment. Knowing that there is no promise of making another jean like this, the detailing takes even the MIJ series to a higher plane: iron buttons that will rust, copper rivets that will oxidize, raised belt loops that will fade, a Japanese tan shell cordovan leather patch featuring the “Flower of Carnage” logo, the MIJ maple leaf embroidered onto the back pocket, the micro busted outseam, the vintage pink selvedge ID, the selvedge button fly.  Dyed, woven, cut, sewn, built in Japan. The Super Guy is a skinny fit with a medium rise, a slim top block, and a taper from knee to hem. Each pair will be delivered in a beautifully made jointed construction pine box. 
 16oz Japanese Selvedge Denim 
 100% Cotton 
 
 Made in Japan 
 SKU: 101565600
name: MIJ8 - Tokushima Natural Indigo Hand Dyed Intangible Cultural Treasure Selvedge Denim

description_bullet: Made in Japan,SKU: NFMIJ05TT
description_paragraph:
The MIJ5 Kogare Kakishibu is a 14.5oz short slub Japanese selvedge denim with indigo dyed exterior warp and Kakishibu dyed interior weft.  Kakishubu dying is a traditional Japanese dye method which utilizes “Kaki” (the Japanese word for persimmon) a small orange fruit that produces an incredible range of orange and brown tones.  For this denim a deep brown dubbed “Kogare” (Japanese for burnt) was used to make up the interior weft yarns.  This denim is unsanforized, however a special Tenpi wash treatment was applied to preshrink and preserve the natural rigidness and beauty of the fabric. There is no need to pre-soak this denim, it is ready to wear from the first day.  Other details include, signature red maple leaf pocket embroidery, 10oz vegetable tanned leather patch with “Flower of Carnage” logo, white ear selvedge ID with an orange running stitch embroidery, 100% iron buttons and copper rivets.  The Super Guy is a slim tapered fit; medium rise, slim thigh and taper from the knee to hem. 
 100% Cotton

description_paragraph:
The Milk Selvedge is a 12.5oz Japanese selvedge denim made with a blend of cotton and 23% actual milk yarn! In a special process, proteins found in the amino acids of milk are drawn out, kneaded then pressed into a fiber. This fiber is then spun into yarn. What makes milk yarn so special is it’s silky smooth and cool feel. When woven into this denim, the fabric feels like a classic rigid raw denim jean, but has a cool touch and silky smoothness. After wash, the denim becomes even more soft and comfortable. Other details include contrast stitching, hair on cow hide leather patch, cow print pocket bags, classic red line ID, and silver metallic buttons and rivets. description_bullet:
12.5oz Japanese Selvedge Denim,100% Cotton,Made in ,
,SKU: ,
description_paragraph:
The Cerulean Kasuri is a 12.5oz Japanese denim with a red line selvedge ID. The warp yarns are dyed using the traditional Japanese Kasuri method. Cotton yarns are wrapped and bound tightly in sections before being dipped in indigo dye, so only the unbound sections can absorb the indigo. After each dip, the binding is removed and other sections are bound, and the yarn is dipped in indigo again. Dyers repeat this process several times to create warp yarns that each have an irregular unique spectrum of indigo shades, dipped to near black in some places and vibrant blues in others. Weaving these section dyed indigo yarns along with white weft yarns creates a fabric with a spectacular variety of indigo shades reminiscent of rain falling heavier and lighter in different places. Cut, sewn, built in Canada with contrast stitching, a navy leather patch, and silver metallic buttons and rivets  The Super Guy is a skinny fit with a medium rise, a slim top block, and a taper from knee to hem.
